\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 08, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104rtx1665702772229.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rtx1665702772229.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/rtx1665702772229.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"rtx1665702772229\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"rtx1665702772229__spawn_241327\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Pass the specified command to the operating system.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"rtx1665702772229__topic_d77564e1_d77565e1_d77566e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rtx1665702772229__p_d77567e1_d77568e1_d77569e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">spawn</span>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">OSCommand</var>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section p\" id=\"rtx1665702772229__section_w2296ab1b7b5_w2297ab1b7_w2298ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rtx1665702772229__p_d77570e1_d77571e1_d77572e1\">Example: <code class=\"ph codeph\">spawn \"rm -i *.p[0-9][0-9] \"</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rtx1665702772229__topic_d51027e1_d51028e1_d51029e1_d51030e1_d51031e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1216565e77\">Parameters</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"rtx1665702772229__table_d7490e1_d7491e1_d7492e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Parameters</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"rtx1665702772229__table_d7490e1_d7491e1_d7492e1__entry__1\">\n Parameter\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"rtx1665702772229__table_d7490e1_d7491e1_d7492e1__entry__2\">\n Data Type\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"rtx1665702772229__table_d7490e1_d7491e1_d7492e1__entry__3\">\n Description\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rtx1665702772229__table_d7490e1_d7491e1_d7492e1__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">OSCommand</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rtx1665702772229__table_d7490e1_d7491e1_d7492e1__entry__2\">\n String\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rtx1665702772229__table_d7490e1_d7491e1_d7492e1__entry__3\">\n Operating system command. The string can be up to 2047 bytes.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rtx1665702772229__topic_d51032e1_d51033e1_d51034e1_d51035e1_d51036e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1216565e131\">Return Values</h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"rtx1665702772229__table_d7493e1_d7494e1_d7495e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Values returned in <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$status</span>\n</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"rtx1665702772229__table_d7493e1_d7494e1_d7495e1__entry__1\">\n Value\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"rtx1665702772229__table_d7493e1_d7494e1_d7495e1__entry__2\">\n Meaning\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rtx1665702772229__table_d7493e1_d7494e1_d7495e1__entry__1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;0</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rtx1665702772229__table_d7493e1_d7494e1_d7495e1__entry__2\">\n An operating system error occurred.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rtx1665702772229__table_d7493e1_d7494e1_d7495e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">0</code>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"rtx1665702772229__table_d7493e1_d7494e1_d7495e1__entry__2\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">OSCommand</var> was successfully spawned. <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$result</span> is set to the value returned by <var class=\"keyword varname\">OSCommand</var>.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rtx1665702772229__topic_d51037e1_d51038e1_d51039e1_d51040e1_d51041e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1216565e201\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rtx1665702772229__d5916e20\">Allowed in all component types.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rtx1665702772229__topic_d51042e1_d51043e1_d51044e1_d51045e1_d51046e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1216565e210\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rtx1665702772229__p_d77588e1_d77589e1_d77590e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">spawn</span> statement clears the screen and passes the <var class=\"keyword varname\">OSCommand</var> to the operating system on which the application is running. In a client/server environment, this is the client machine.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rtx1665702772229__p_d77591e1_d77592e1_d77593e1\">You may need to use the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">refresh</span> statement to repaint the Uniface screen following <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">spawn</span>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rtx1665702772229__p_d77594e1_d77595e1_d77596e1\">The <var class=\"keyword varname\">OSCommand</var> is spawned as an asynchronous process, making it appropriate for interactive applications. To run a synchronous OS command and catch the result, implement an OS service and use <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">activate</span> to call the <code class=\"ph codeph\">COMMAND</code> operation on the service.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rtx1665702772229__topic_d51047e1_d51048e1_d51049e1_d51050e1_d51051e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1216565e246\">Windows</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rtx1665702772229__p_d77600e1_d77601e1_d77602e1\">On Microsoft Windows platforms, you can spawn the command as a synchronous process by prefixing the command with a hash character (#). In the following example, the Uniface application is suspended until the program <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">conv_val</span> ends:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">; start conv_val to convert file specified in vFile\nspawn \"#conv_val.exe %%vFile.raw\"\n; load processed values into vValues\nfileload \"%%$1.dat\",vValues\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rtx1665702772229__section_g2c_ghm_zbc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1216565e261\">Unix</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rtx1665702772229__p_d77606e1_d77607e1_d77608e1\">Under Unix, a spawned process that detaches itself\n            from the parent process can be used for interprocess communication.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rtx1665702772229__p_d77609e1_d77610e1_d77611e1\">You can spawn the command as a synchronous process\n            using the standard command:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"rtx1665702772229__pre_h3s_hhm_zbc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">spawn</span>  <var class=\"keyword varname\">OSCommand</var></code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"rtx1665702772229__p_d77612e1_d77613e1_d77614e1\">You can also spawn the command as an asynchronous call\n            by using the ampersand character (&amp;) at the end of the command:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"rtx1665702772229__pre_j3s_hhm_zbc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\"><span class=\"keyword cmdname\">spawn</span>  <var class=\"keyword varname\">OSCommand</var>&amp;</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rtx1665702772229__section_ixw_3hm_zbc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1216565e292\">Example: Interactively Removing Print Files </h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The following example uses the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">spawn</span> statement to\n            interactively remove any print files (those ending in <span class=\"ph filepath\">.p00</span> through\n               <span class=\"ph filepath\">.p99</span>). This example uses the Unix <code class=\"ph codeph\">rm</code> command,\n            which should be in the user's path (Unix systems only).</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"rtx1665702772229__pre_ckl_lhm_zbc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">trigger detail\nspawn \"rm -i *.p[0-9][0-9] \"\naskmess \"Press space bar to return.\",\" \",-1\nrefresh\nend</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"rtx1665702772229__topic_d51052e1_d51053e1_d51054e1_d51055e1_d51056e1\">\n<div class=\"div\">\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/whl1665702772305.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>refresh</a><p>Redraw the current Form component in character mode only.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ncx1686824523526.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$result</a><p>Return the result of certain ProcScript commands and tree widget events.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531787\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2531787\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "spawn Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 08, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Pass the specified command to the operating system. spawn OSCommand Example: spawn \"rm -i *.p[0-9][0-9] \" Parameters Table 1. Parameters Parameter Data Type Description OSCommand String Operating system command. The string can be up to 2047 bytes. Return Values Table 2. Values returned in $status Value Meaning <0 An operating system error occurred. 0 OSCommand was successfully spawned. $result is set to the value returned by OSCommand . Use Allowed in all component types. Description The spawn statement clears the screen and passes the OSCommand to the operating system on which the application is running. In a client/server environment, this is the client machine. You may need to use the refresh statement to repaint the Uniface screen following spawn . The OSCommand is spawned as an asynchronous process, making it appropriate for interactive applications. To run a synchronous OS command and catch the result, implement an OS service and use activate to call the COMMAND operation on the service. Windows On Microsoft Windows platforms, you can spawn the command as a synchronous process by prefixing the command with a hash character (#). In the following example, the Uniface application is suspended until the program conv_val ends: ; start conv_val to convert file specified in vFile spawn \"#conv_val.exe %%vFile.raw\" ; load processed values into vValues fileload \"%%$1.dat\",vValues Copy Unix Under Unix, a spawned process that detaches itself from the parent process can be used for interprocess communication. You can spawn the command as a synchronous process using the standard command: spawn OSCommand Copy You can also spawn the command as an asynchronous call by using the ampersand character (&) at the end of the command: spawn OSCommand & Copy Example: Interactively Removing Print Files The following example uses the spawn statement to interactively remove any print files (those ending in .p00 through .p99 ). This example uses the Unix rm command, which should be in the user's path (Unix systems only). trigger detail spawn \"rm -i *.p[0-9][0-9] \" askmess \"Press space bar to return.\",\" \",-1 refresh end Copy Related Links refresh Redraw the current Form component in character mode only. $result Return the result of certain ProcScript commands and tree widget events. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}